The paper discusses the design and implementation of a new routing link metric for wireless multihop networks, which falls under the category of network protocols and algorithms. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the computational burden of a metric and its impact on protocol performance, which could fall under the sub-categories of cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also analyzes the requirements for designing a new link metric, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of the implemented link metric, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning).
